
[1]astringent

   ASTRING'ENT, a. Binding; contracting; strengthening; opposed to
   laxative.

   ASTRING'ENT, n. a medicine which binds or contracts the parts of the
   body to which it is applied, restrains profuse discharges, coagulates
   animal fluids, condenses and strengthens the solids.

   Modern practice inclines to the use of astringent, for internal
   applications, and styptic, for external.
